# Dockerfile build-context filter (Task 15.1).
#
# Goal: keep the build context lean so `docker build` ships only what
# we genuinely need to compile + bundle. The runtime image is assembled
# from the build stage's output, so anything not required for `npm ci`
# / `npm run build` should be excluded.
#
# Important quirk: `**/*.tsx` would also strip the SPA sources that
# `esbuild src/plugin/dashboard/spa/index.tsx` reads at build time, so
# we DO NOT add that pattern. The bundled `src/plugin/dashboard/public/app.js`
# (an emitted JS bundle, not a TSX source) is generated inside the
# build stage from the .tsx sources, so both must be in the context.

node_modules
dist
.git
.kiro
.tmp-assets
.smoke-data
tests
coverage
*.log
**/.DS_Store

# Test files: per-file `*.test.ts` only — keep .tsx for SPA sources.
**/*.test.ts

# Editor / OS noise
.vscode
.idea
Thumbs.db

# Build outputs that the build stage regenerates anyway. We leave the
# checked-in HTML and CSS in the context — they are inputs, not outputs.
src/plugin/dashboard/public/app.js
src/plugin/dashboard/public/app.js.map

# Local dev artifacts
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
